WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.500
Digital Tale of Genji - Feature Introduction.

00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.000
We will explain "Viewing Images and Text Together."

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:05.500
Access "View Images and Text Together" from the menu.

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:08.000
Click the menu item on the left side.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:11.000
This is the top page.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:14.000
You can browse the following images.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
The Tale of Genji (Todai manuscript) and Old Movable Type Edition (Kyudai manuscript).

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Muketsu Mukankisheihanbon, Kogetsusho, and Koigenji Monogatari.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Click "View Images and Text Together" to open the viewer.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.500
You can access each resource with one click via "Related Links."

00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:25.000
Links to Koigenji Monogatari, modern translations, and Shinpen Nihon Koten Bungaku Zenshu.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.500
This is the screen for viewing original images and text together.

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:29.500
A Parallel Text Viewer utilizing TEI and IIIF.

00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:32.000
Original images on the left, main text on the upper right, modern translation on the lower right.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Unwanted images can be hidden with the "x" button.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Closing images one by one.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:42.000
You can display only the original images you need in a larger view.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:47.000
You can compare the Todai and Kyudai old movable type manuscripts side by side.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:56.000
This allows comparison between different manuscripts.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.500
We will introduce how to read related materials via original images.

00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:01.000
Please note the ginkgo leaf marks on the images.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Orange ginkgo marks link to the Koigenji Monogatari.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
Blue ginkgo marks link to the Shinpen Nihon Koten Bungaku Zenshu.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:07.000
Hover over them to see the link destination.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:09.000
Click the orange ginkgo mark to access the Koigenji Monogatari.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:13.000
You can zoom in on the Todai manuscript image for detailed viewing.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Clicking opens the National Diet Library Digital Collection.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:23.000
The page is loading.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:28.000
The corresponding page of the Koigenji Monogatari is now displayed.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:33.000
You can view it on the National Diet Library Digital Collection.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.500
Next, click the blue ginkgo mark.

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:40.000
This links to the Shinpen Nihon Koten Bungaku Zenshu.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.000
JapanKnowledge offers both a Lib edition and a Personal edition.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:50.000
Clicking the blue ginkgo mark opens JapanKnowledge.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:55.000
You can read the Shinpen Nihon Koten Bungaku Zenshu text on JapanKnowledge Lib.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:02:00.000
For the Personal edition, please log in with your own account.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
After logging in, you can view the corresponding sections.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.000
Here is how to view the Tale of Genji via the Koigenji Monogatari.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:09.000
IIIF icons are displayed at the top of each page.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:13.000
Clicking the IIIF icon displays the corresponding section of the original images.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.000
The original images are displayed automatically.

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:21.000
Multiple original images are shown side by side.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:25.000
You can compare corresponding sections across different manuscripts.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.500
Orange ginkgo marks indicate the corresponding sections.

00:02:27.500 --> 00:02:30.000
You can compare multiple manuscripts simultaneously.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:32.500
Let us explain the anchor marks.

00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:35.000
They are displayed at the beginning of each line in the Koigenji Monogatari.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:37.500
Clicking highlights the corresponding section in the modern translation.

00:02:37.500 --> 00:02:40.000
Hovering over the modern translation highlights the corresponding anchor mark.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:43.500
Digital Tale of Genji.

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:47.000
Thank you for watching.
